  A lot of what we do with CSS is to set fonts and colors. Here are some examples: There are plenty of other properties that can be set, in much the same way.     Sizes &lt;style&gt; p.fixed { font-size: 20px; background-color: gray; } p.em-small { font-size: 0.6em; background-color: blue; } p.em-big { font-size: 2em; background-color: red; } div.pixel-box { width: 70px; height: 70px; border: 1px solid black; } div.percent-box { width: 20%; height: 30px; border: 1px solid black; } div.viewport-box { width: 30vw; height: 30vh; border: 1px solid black; } &lt;/style&gt; &lt;p class="fixed"&gt;This paragraph will follow the rules in p.fixed -- size 20px&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p class="em-small"&gt;This paragraph will follow the rules in p.em-small -- size 0.6em&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p class="em-big"&gt;This paragraph will follow the rules in p.em-big: 2em&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div class="pixel-box"&gt;.pixel-box&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="percent-box"&gt;.percent-box&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="viewport-box"&gt;.viewport-box&lt;/div&gt;     function shadowizecss_sizes () {var elId="css_sizes"; var dom_block="
